Two vehicles were involved in an accident earlier this morning (Saturday) on the corner of Rissik and Voortrekker. According to eyewitnesses on the scene, this occurred around 10:00 and emergency medical service personnel just arrived. A family car collided with a taxi. It was learnt that only a driver was in the taxi while two people were traveling in the other vehicle. A woman suffered head injuries while the driver of the taxi has shown no signs of injuries, eyewitnesses explained.